<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Tarpeian" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Tarpeian,</orth> pertaining to the rocky steep in ancient Rome, from which criminals were precipitated: <cit><quote>bear him to the rock T.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 213</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the T. rock,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.213" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 213</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 3</bibl>. <cit><quote>the steep T. death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.88" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 88</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the rock T.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.88" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 88</bibl></cit>
